2 SENATE BILL 887
1 (a) (1) This section does not apply to Baltimore City.
2 (2) Subsections (b), (c), (d), and (f) of this section do not apply in Prince
3 George’s County.
4 (b) (1) The term of a county superintendent is 4 years beginning on July 1. A
5 county superintendent continues to serve until a successor is appointed and qualifies.
6 (2) [By February 1 of the year in which a term ends, the county
7 superintendent shall notify the county board whether the superintendent is a candidate for
8 reappointment.
9 (3)] (I) [In] SUBJECT TO SUBPARAGRAPH (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH,
10 IN the year in which [a] AN INITIAL term begins, the county board shall appoint a county
11 superintendent between February 1 and June 30. [However, if the county board decides to
12 reappoint the incumbent superintendent, the county board shall take final action at a
13 public meeting no later than March 1 of that year.]
14 (II) AT ANY POINT DURING THE INCUMBENT
15 SUPERINTENDENT’S TERM, THE THE COUNTY BOARD MAY TAKE ACTION AT A PUBLIC
16 MEETING TO REAPPOINT THE INCUMBENT SUPERINTENDENT AT ANY TIME AFTER
17 THE END OF THE SECOND YEAR OF THE INCUMBENT SUPERINTENDENT’S TERM BUT
18 NOT LATER THAN MARCH 1 OF THE YEAR IN WHICH THE CONTRACT IS BEING
19 RENEWED TO REAPPOINT THE INCUMBENT SUPERINTENDENT TO SERVE A NEW
20 TERM OF 4 YEARS BEGINNING THE IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING JULY 1.
21 [(4)] (3) If a county board is unable to appoint a county superintendent
22 by July 1 of a year in which a term begins, the provisions of subsection (d) of this section
23 apply.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
25 1, 2025.

